Name: Marina Q1 - Lot 318 Beckworth Boulevard
Description:
Everything about the Marina is designed for effortless family living. Practical touches like a spacious butler?s pantry hidden from view behind the kitchen, integrated, open-plan living spaces and smaller, but just as important, features like the generous walk-in-linen closet make this home easy to live in and love.

The whole family will enjoy meals and gatherings in the open plan living-dining-kitchen area. The stunning, stone island kitchen

bench is a focal point and doubles as a breakfast bar or servery when entertaining. In keeping with the practical nature of this home, there?s a large butler?s pantry behind the kitchen for food storage and preparation and a place to hide away the fridge.

If a little peace and quiet is needed, family members can retreat to the home theatre down the hall, which is neatly positioned between the sleeping zones. This flexible room can be used for watching movies, playing games, studying, music or relaxing.
Parents will enjoy their own space with a generous master suite conveniently placed at the front for seclusion and light. Featuring a large walk-in robe and an ensuite with separate toilet and twin basins, this functional area also offers a touch of luxury.

Three more bedrooms are positioned to the rear of the home and all feature built in robes to help keep rooms neat and spacious. A centrally located bathroom is appointed with vanity, bath and shower plus a separate powder room. This means no queuing for the facilities ? which is sure to result in a peaceful household! The powder room also provides convenience for guests when entertaining. A large, centrally located linen closet provides extra storage ? yet another practical addition to this home.

With an abundance of well-placed practical features, the Marina is an easy living, stylish family home.

Name: Monterey Belle Q2 - Lot 1224 Dexter Crescent
Lexington Lux Q1 Mk2 - Lot 622 Cascarilla Street
Description:
The minute you step through the Lexington?s doors, you will instantly notice the beautiful lines and contours of this gorgeous home, leaving you with a feeling of luxury and grandeur.

 Among other features, the cleverly designed Lexington Series offers multiple entertaining options with its impeccably appointed kitchen that will surely delight the most avid of entertainers.

 From the European styled designer kitchen, you will look out to the family living and meals areas, which allows you the versatility to entertain even the most boisterous crowds, or to cater more intimate occasions if the mood takes you.

 If you are looking to entertain an even larger crowd the Lexington can take you and your guests a step further?or better yet, outside! With a bright and refreshing undercover alfresco area, you can sit and chat or simply unwind. Like anything else in life balance is key, and to achieve it the Lexington Series has also been designed with privacy in mind.
 With the master suite nestled away from the main entertaining areas, you will feel like you have been taken away to a five-star resort. The impressive ensuite and generous dressing room, combined with a spacious bedroom, will leave you living in the lap of luxury, making your room the perfect setting for some peace and relaxation.

 The additional three bedrooms have also been tucked away from the day?s hustle and bustle, with the Lexington Lux Q1 also offering an additional reading area. Bonding the three rooms and bathroom together, this study nook will separate the kids? space from the rest of the home.

The Lexington Series has been designed for luxury living and extravagance, but still offers versatility and comfort that will not disappoint.

Name: Monaco Nouveau Q1 Mk2 - Lot 608 Calibre Circuit
Description:
The Monaco will be your heaven with its tasteful and captivating design bringing happiness and joy to your family home.

The Monaco has been designed to encompass both functionality and class. The faultlessly appointed kitchen will provide a centrepiece to the living and dining areas, for you, your family and friends to take pleasure in. While overlooking a large and bright meals area, sleek stainless steel appliances and superior quality finishes will ensure a myriad of family dinners full of delicious dishes, laughter and wonderful memories. With easy access to the laundry, all domestic necessities are at your fingertips.  
Family living is further enhanced by the kids retreat or TV area, which is sure to be a popular place to come together and chill out with the kids. The additional three bedrooms, all with built-in robes are situated in close proximity to the family bathroom with separate toilet, meaning family and guests will always feel at home in the Monaco.

You will be delighted by the master suite, with its walk-in robe and impressive ensuite. Discover its calming powers, as the ensuite embraces you in a relaxing atmosphere. A slick his & hers double vanity means no room for arguments over who puts what where, and plenty of space for your fragrances, salts and potions to dissipate the day's cares. 

The Monaco combines beauty and functionality to create a paradise of a home. 

-	All site cost included (no hidden extras)
-	Estate covenants, guidelines & local council requirements
-	Carpet & timber look flooring
-	Choice of colours & finishes
-	Professional interior design service consultation
-	50 year structural guarantee
-	Minimum 6 star energy rating
-	Free home loan finance consultation

Name: Mercer Q1 - Lot 2028 Carissa Road
Description:
Delightfully light, deceptively large and fully equipped with all the luxury touches, the Mercer is for families who like to live on a truly magnificent scale!

From the moment you step inside from the covered porch, you get a sense of just how grand this home is. A wide hallway leads you past a spacious study, huge home theatre and smart dining room to the open plan kitchen, living and dining area. Here the light floods in from the generously proportioned windows and reflects off the polished floors and stone bench tops. This free-flowing area easily accommodates everything from big get-togethers to games nights or casual family meals all year round.

In warm weather, slide back the large glass doors to reveal an undercover alfresco dining deck perfect for sunny lunches or summer nights.
Formal occasions are well catered for as well, with the central grand island kitchen bench just made for serving, and the large butler?s pantry perfect for preparation and storage. The formal dining room is nearby and has easy access to the downstairs powder room for guests? convenience.

Upstairs, everyone has his or her own personal space; none more than the parents with a simply palatial master suite. An open area at the top of the stairs is suitable for a TV lounge or study area and leads to three bedrooms, all with built-in robes. The centrally located and spacious bathroom has a shower and bath plus separate powder room, so there?s no lining up!

The sprawling master suite takes up the rest of the top floor. There?s a walk-in robe nearly as big as a bedroom with three sides of storage you?ll be challenged to fill. An ensuite with twin basins, separate toilet, large bath and extra-large shower gives you so much room you?ll think you are in a penthouse bathroom!

If you?re looking for all that life can offer, there?s nothing as generous as the Mercer.

Name: Lexington Lux Q1 Mk2 - Lot 721 Richmond Street
Description:
The minute you step through the Lexington?s doors, you will instantly notice the beautiful lines and contours of this gorgeous home, leaving you with a feeling of luxury and grandeur.

 Among other features, the cleverly designed Lexington Series offers multiple entertaining options with its impeccably appointed kitchen that will surely delight the most avid of entertainers.

 From the European styled designer kitchen, you will look out to the family living and meals areas, which allows you the versatility to entertain even the most boisterous crowds, or to cater more intimate occasions if the mood takes you.

 If you are looking to entertain an even larger crowd the Lexington can take you and your guests a step further?or better yet, outside! With a bright and refreshing undercover alfresco area, you can sit and chat or simply unwind. Like anything else in life balance is key, and to achieve it the Lexington Series has also been designed with privacy in mind.
 With the master suite nestled away from the main entertaining areas, you will feel like you have been taken away to a five-star resort. The impressive ensuite and generous dressing room, combined with a spacious bedroom, will leave you living in the lap of luxury, making your room the perfect setting for some peace and relaxation.

 The additional three bedrooms have also been tucked away from the day?s hustle and bustle, with the Lexington Lux Q1 also offering an additional reading area. Bonding the three rooms and bathroom together, this study nook will separate the kids? space from the rest of the home.

The Lexington Series has been designed for luxury living and extravagance, but still offers versatility and comfort that will not disappoint.

Name: Allegra Q2 - Lot 415 Middleton Drive
Description: Generous proportions, wide-open spaces, private getaways and an abundance of bathrooms are just some of the reasons why the Allegra is the definitive luxury family home. On the ground floor you?ll find the perfect layout with four separate living areas, starting with the home theatre off the entrance, then the study a little further down the hall. An open plan kitchen, dining and family area lead onto the fourth break-out space ? a wide undercover alfresco deck. In summer open the doors wide and this living space seems to stretch forever. Tucked behind the living quarter, accessed by a private hallway, lies the most indulgent feature of this home: an extravagant master suite. Here you?ll find more storage than you?ll ever need, with an enormous dressing room augmented by triple built-in robes opposite the ensuite. A separate bath, his and hers basins and separate toilet means two can happily enjoy the bathroom area at the one time, with plenty of space and privacy. Upstairs are three further bedrooms, two with walk-in robes and one with a second ensuite ? which makes it perfect for older children, grandparents or visitors. There?s also a large leisure area for studying, playing or relaxing, plus a spacious central bathroom with separate powder room. There?s only one thing this home offers more of than getaway spaces, and that?s storage places. There are walk-in linen cupboards upstairs and down, a huge laundry with access to outside on the ground floor and, off the kitchen, a superbly appointed butler?s pantry with enough bench space to plate up for the largest parties. With every little detail covered in a big way, the Allegra is built to impress and designed to please

Name: Monaco Lux Q1 - Lot 605 Calibre Circuit
Marina Q1 - Lot 314 Beckworth Boulevard
Description:
Everything about the Marina is designed for effortless family living. Practical touches like a spacious butler?s pantry hidden from view behind the kitchen, integrated, open-plan living spaces and smaller, but just as important, features like the generous walk-in-linen closet make this home easy to live in and love.

The whole family will enjoy meals and gatherings in the open plan living-dining-kitchen area. The stunning, stone island kitchen

bench is a focal point and doubles as a breakfast bar or servery when entertaining. In keeping with the practical nature of this home, there?s a large butler?s pantry behind the kitchen for food storage and preparation and a place to hide away the fridge.

If a little peace and quiet is needed, family members can retreat to the home theatre down the hall, which is neatly positioned between the sleeping zones. This flexible room can be used for watching movies, playing games, studying, music or relaxing.
Parents will enjoy their own space with a generous master suite conveniently placed at the front for seclusion and light. Featuring a large walk-in robe and an ensuite with separate toilet and twin basins, this functional area also offers a touch of luxury.

Three more bedrooms are positioned to the rear of the home and all feature built in robes to help keep rooms neat and spacious. A centrally located bathroom is appointed with vanity, bath and shower plus a separate powder room. This means no queuing for the facilities ? which is sure to result in a peaceful household! The powder room also provides convenience for guests when entertaining. A large, centrally located linen closet provides extra storage ? yet another practical addition to this home.

With an abundance of well-placed practical features, the Marina is an easy living, stylish family home.

Name: Carmelle Q1 - Lot 538 Horizon Boulevard
Description:
Effortless style, integrated living zones and interior flair make the Carmelle a unique family home.

The carefully considered design with central integrated living, allows the family to come together for casual family meals and entertainment, yet still permits each member to enjoy their own space.

An emphasis on functionality is clearly reflected in the large laundry and well laid out kitchen. The laundry has room for the biggest piles of washing and opens to the side of the house for easy access to the outdoors. Function and style continues into the kitchen with an impressive grand island bench that doubles as a breakfast bar and servery. Food and dishes can be kept out of sight in the butler's pantry, which is easily accessed from the garage for swift delivery of groceries. Generous bench space either side of the cooktop makes preparing large dinners a breeze.
Sprawling from this central kitchen hub is a plethora of spacious living, dining, and entertainment spaces. Entertainment is very much on the agenda in this family home with indoor and outdoor dining options including an undercover alfresco as well as three more separate entertainment areas including a home theatre, kids retreat and living room.

The master bedroom at the front of the house also doubles as a parentss retreat and boasts a large walk-in wardrobe plus ensuite featuring his and her basins.

Three further bedrooms are located at the other end of the house, one with a walk-in robe, the others with built-in wardrobes to keep clothes neatly tucked away. These generously sized double bedrooms each open out onto a kid's retreat perfect for the kids to relax and play. The well-proportioned main bathroom with shower and bath is positioned across the hall from the powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Name: Geneva Q1 - Lot 731 Newbridge Boulevard
Description:
Created to impress but designed for function, the Geneva delivers something special for every member of the family. Parents will love the palatial Master Suite privately nestled at the rear of the house, kids will appreciate the spacious bedrooms all with built-in robes and with three entertaining zones there?s a place for everyone to escape.

It?s not just the clever layout that makes the Geneva so liveable; it?s all the finishing touches too. The main bathroom has its own separate powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time. While the master ensuite includes ?his and hers? basins and a dressing room big enough for two, so there?s plenty of room to get ready without crowding. For families who love to entertain, the Geneva is really impressive. The free flowing kitchen, dining and family area is perfect for large gatherings, and the open plan allows for social interaction while preparing or serving in the European styled designer kitchen. Kids will love sitting up at the island kitchen bench for meals and for those fine dining occasions, the generous butler?s pantry in the corner means food items and preparation can be kept cleverly out of sight.

Relaxing is so much easier when you?re not on top of each other, so the Geneva has a family room plus a separate theatre which can double as a TV room or games room. With a large undercover alfresco deck opening out from the theatre it?s ideal for parties.

Life is too short to compromise - which is why the Geneva series makes it easy to have comfort, style and convenience all under the one roof.

Description:
Created to impress but designed for function, the Geneva delivers something special for every member of the family. Parents will love the palatial Master Suite privately nestled at the rear of the house, kids will appreciate the spacious bedrooms all with built-in robes and with three entertaining zones there?s a place for everyone to escape.

For families who love to entertain, the Geneva is really impressive. Kids will love sitting up at the island kitchen bench for meals and for those fine dining occasions, the generous butler?s pantry in the corner means food items and preparation can be kept cleverly out of sight.

Relaxing is so much easier when you?re not on top of each other, so the Geneva has a family room plus a separate theatre which can double as a TV room or games room. With a large undercover alfresco deck opening out from the theatre it?s ideal for parties.

Life is too short to compromise - which is why the Geneva series makes it easy to have comfort, style and convenience all under the one roof.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Name: Monterey Nouveau Q1 Mk2 - Lot 1224 Dexter Crescent
Description:
An energetically modern and chic single storey home that offers all the luxuries and superior features previously only available in a large double storey home, makes the Monterey Series a best seller in its own right.

 Upon entering the Monterey, you will inevitably notice its ingenious and contemporary design. At the front of the home, take some time out in the plush atmosphere of the master suite, with its own walk-in robe and a striking ensuite offering a double vanity and secluded large shower. Only a few steps away from the master suite, you will find the study, ideal for a quiet moment away from it all.

 Stroll out and you will be greeted by a luxurious living area, leading you into the hub of this home. Surrounded by a theatre, dining, living and undercover alfresco area, the dazzling designer kitchen will become the perfect backdrop for the globe-trotting master chef wanting to whip up that secret signature dish.
 And for those with too many recipes to remember, and an even longer list of friends wanting a taste, the Monterey offers a generous butler?s pantry for added storage room for large dinner parties. The Monterey Series is the idyllic choice for families in need of space with secondary double-sized bedrooms all with built-in robes. A bathroom with a deep bath and separate toilet is another thoughtful touch for a growing family.

 The Monterey Nouveau Q1 also offers additional space for a home frequently visited by friends, family and neighbours, boasting an extra powder room and additional hallway that connects all the bedrooms while also separating them from the livelier entertaining areas. This makes the Monterey a serene haven, encapsulating elegant, inspired design.

Name: Mercer Q1 - Lot 2027 Carissa Road
Description:
Delightfully light, deceptively large and fully equipped with all the luxury touches, the Mercer is for families who like to live on a truly magnificent scale!

From the moment you step inside from the covered porch, you get a sense of just how grand this home is. A wide hallway leads you past a spacious study, huge home theatre and smart dining room to the open plan kitchen, living and dining area. Here the light floods in from the generously proportioned windows and reflects off the polished floors and stone bench tops. This free-flowing area easily accommodates everything from big get-togethers to games nights or casual family meals all year round.

In warm weather, slide back the large glass doors to reveal an undercover alfresco dining deck perfect for sunny lunches or summer nights.
Formal occasions are well catered for as well, with the central grand island kitchen bench just made for serving, and the large butler?s pantry perfect for preparation and storage. The formal dining room is nearby and has easy access to the downstairs powder room for guests? convenience.

Upstairs, everyone has his or her own personal space; none more than the parents with a simply palatial master suite. An open area at the top of the stairs is suitable for a TV lounge or study area and leads to three bedrooms, all with built-in robes. The centrally located and spacious bathroom has a shower and bath plus separate powder room, so there?s no lining up!

The sprawling master suite takes up the rest of the top floor. There?s a walk-in robe nearly as big as a bedroom with three sides of storage you?ll be challenged to fill. An ensuite with twin basins, separate toilet, large bath and extra-large shower gives you so much room you?ll think you are in a penthouse bathroom!

If you?re looking for all that life can offer, there?s nothing as generous as the Mercer.

Name: Carmelle Q1 - Lot 647 Tamarind Place
Description:
Effortless style, integrated living zones and interior flair make the Carmelle a unique family home.

The carefully considered design with central integrated living, allows the family to come together for casual family meals and entertainment, yet still permits each member to enjoy their own space.

An emphasis on functionality is clearly reflected in the large laundry and well laid out kitchen. The laundry has room for the biggest piles of washing and opens to the side of the house for easy access to the outdoors. Function and style continues into the kitchen with an impressive grand island bench that doubles as a breakfast bar and servery. Food and dishes can be kept out of sight in the butler?s pantry, which is easily accessed from the garage for swift delivery of groceries. Generous bench space either side of the cooktop makes preparing large dinners a breeze.
Sprawling from this central kitchen hub is a plethora of spacious living, dining, and entertainment spaces. Entertainment is very much on the agenda in this family home with indoor and outdoor dining options including an undercover alfresco as well as three more separate entertainment areas including a home theatre, kids retreat and living room.

The master bedroom at the front of the house also doubles as a parents? retreat and boasts a large walk-in wardrobe plus ensuite featuring his and her basins.

Three further bedrooms are located at the other end of the house, one with a walk-in robe, the others with built-in wardrobes to keep clothes neatly tucked away. These generously sized double bedrooms each open out onto a kid?s retreat perfect for the kids to relax and play. The well-proportioned main bathroom with shower and bath is positioned across the hall from the powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Name: Vogue Q1 - Lot 31705 Water Lily Circuit
Mercer Q3 - Lot 2028 Carissa Road
Description:
Delightfully light, deceptively large and fully equipped with all the luxury touches, the Mercer is for families who like to live on a truly magnificent scale!

From the moment you step inside from the covered porch, you get a sense of just how grand this home is. A wide hallway leads you past a spacious study, huge home theatre and smart dining room to the open plan kitchen, living and dining area. Here the light floods in from the generously proportioned windows and reflects off the polished floors and stone bench tops. This free-flowing area easily accommodates everything from big get-togethers to games nights or casual family meals all year round.

In warm weather, slide back the large glass doors to reveal an undercover alfresco dining deck perfect for sunny lunches or summer nights.
Formal occasions are well catered for as well, with the central grand island kitchen bench just made for serving, and the large butler?s pantry perfect for preparation and storage. The formal dining room is nearby and has easy access to the downstairs powder room for guests? convenience.

Upstairs, everyone has his or her own personal space; none more than the parents with a simply palatial master suite. An open area at the top of the stairs is suitable for a TV lounge or study area and leads to three bedrooms, all with built-in robes. The centrally located and spacious bathroom has a shower and bath plus separate powder room, so there?s no lining up!

The sprawling master suite takes up the rest of the top floor. There?s a walk-in robe nearly as big as a bedroom with three sides of storage you?ll be challenged to fill. An ensuite with twin basins, separate toilet, large bath and extra-large shower gives you so much room you?ll think you are in a penthouse bathroom!

If you?re looking for all that life can offer, there?s nothing as generous as the Mercer.

Name: Monaco Lux Q1 - Lot 1414 Rockley Road
Monterey Belle Q2 - Lot 412 Quarter Street
Monterey Lux Q1 - Lot 1224 Dexter Crescent
Allegra Q2 - Lot 2050 Carissa Road
Description: Generous proportions, wide-open spaces, private getaways and an abundance of bathrooms are just some of the reasons why the Allegra is the definitive luxury family home. On the ground floor you?ll find the perfect layout with four separate living areas, starting with the home theatre off the entrance, then the study a little further down the hall. An open plan kitchen, dining and family area lead onto the fourth break-out space ? a wide undercover alfresco deck. In summer open the doors wide and this living space seems to stretch forever. Tucked behind the living quarter, accessed by a private hallway, lies the most indulgent feature of this home: an extravagant master suite. Here you?ll find more storage than you?ll ever need, with an enormous dressing room augmented by triple built-in robes opposite the ensuite. A separate bath, his and hers basins and separate toilet means two can happily enjoy the bathroom area at the one time, with plenty of space and privacy. Upstairs are three further bedrooms, two with walk-in robes and one with a second ensuite ? which makes it perfect for older children, grandparents or visitors. There?s also a large leisure area for studying, playing or relaxing, plus a spacious central bathroom with separate powder room. There?s only one thing this home offers more of than getaway spaces, and that?s storage places. There are walk-in linen cupboards upstairs and down, a huge laundry with access to outside on the ground floor and, off the kitchen, a superbly appointed butler?s pantry with enough bench space to plate up for the largest parties. With every little detail covered in a big way, the Allegra is built to impress and designed to please

Name: Sahara Belle Q1 - Lot 605 Calibre Circuit
Carmelle Q1 - Lot 690 Pioneer Drive
Description:
Effortless style, integrated living zones and interior flair make the Carmelle a unique family home.

The carefully considered design with central integrated living, allows the family to come together for casual family meals and entertainment, yet still permits each member to enjoy their own space.

An emphasis on functionality is clearly reflected in the large laundry and well laid out kitchen. The laundry has room for the biggest piles of washing and opens to the side of the house for easy access to the outdoors. Function and style continues into the kitchen with an impressive grand island bench that doubles as a breakfast bar and servery. Food and dishes can be kept out of sight in the butler?s pantry, which is easily accessed from the garage for swift delivery of groceries. Generous bench space either side of the cooktop makes preparing large dinners a breeze.
Sprawling from this central kitchen hub is a plethora of spacious living, dining, and entertainment spaces. Entertainment is very much on the agenda in this family home with indoor and outdoor dining options including an undercover alfresco as well as three more separate entertainment areas including a home theatre, kids retreat and living room.

The master bedroom at the front of the house also doubles as a parents? retreat and boasts a large walk-in wardrobe plus ensuite featuring his and her basins.

Three further bedrooms are located at the other end of the house, one with a walk-in robe, the others with built-in wardrobes to keep clothes neatly tucked away. These generously sized double bedrooms each open out onto a kid?s retreat perfect for the kids to relax and play. The well-proportioned main bathroom with shower and bath is positioned across the hall from the powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Name: Montana Q2 - Lot 31706 Water Lily Circuit
Description:
The Montana will be your heaven, with its tasteful and captivating design bringing happiness and joy to your family home.

 From the stunning family room to the open dining room, designer kitchen and large theatre room, the Montana is generously proportioned and designed with unity and utility in mind.

 While your friends and family take pleasure in the living, dining and alfresco areas, the faultlessly appointed kitchen provides the centrepiece for your home. Overlooking a large and bright meals area, with sleek stainless steel appliances and superior quality finishes, it provides a perfect backdrop for family dinners filled with delicious dishes, laughter and happy memories. With easy access to the laundry, all domestic necessities are also at your fingertips.
 You will be delighted by the master suite, with its walk-in robe and impressive ensuite. Discover its calming powers, as the ensuite embraces you in a relaxing atmosphere. A slick his & hers double vanity means no need for arguments over who puts what where, and there is plenty of space for all the fragrances, salts and potions you need to dissipate the cares of the day.

 The additional bedrooms, all with built-in robes, are situated in close proximity to the family bathroom with separate toilet, ensuring family and guests will always feel at home in the Montana.

 The Montana combines beauty and functionality to create a paradise of a home.

With every little detail covered in a big way, the Allegra is built to impress and designed to please

Name: Carmelle Q1 - Lot 2028 Carissa Road
Description:
Effortless style, integrated living zones and interior flair make the Carmelle a unique family home.

The carefully considered design with central integrated living, allows the family to come together for casual family meals and entertainment, yet still permits each member to enjoy their own space.

An emphasis on functionality is clearly reflected in the large laundry and well laid out kitchen. The laundry has room for the biggest piles of washing and opens to the side of the house for easy access to the outdoors. Function and style continues into the kitchen with an impressive grand island bench that doubles as a breakfast bar and servery. Food and dishes can be kept out of sight in the butler's pantry, which is easily accessed from the garage for swift delivery of groceries. Generous bench space either side of the cooktop makes preparing large dinners a breeze.
Sprawling from this central kitchen hub is a plethora of spacious living, dining, and entertainment spaces. Entertainment is very much on the agenda in this family home with indoor and outdoor dining options including an undercover alfresco as well as three more separate entertainment areas including a home theatre, kids retreat and living room.

The master bedroom at the front of the house also doubles as a parentss retreat and boasts a large walk-in wardrobe plus ensuite featuring his and her basins.

Three further bedrooms are located at the other end of the house, one with a walk-in robe, the others with built-in wardrobes to keep clothes neatly tucked away. These generously sized double bedrooms each open out onto a kid's retreat perfect for the kids to relax and play. The well-proportioned main bathroom with shower and bath is positioned across the hall from the powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Name: Mercer Q2 - Lot 2027 Carissa Road
Description: Delightfully light, deceptively large and fully equipped with all the luxury touches, the Mercer is for families who like to live on a truly magnificent scale! From the moment you step inside from the covered porch, you get a sense of just how grand this home is. A wide hallway leads you past a spacious study, huge home theatre and smart dining room to the open plan kitchen, living and dining area. Here the light floods in from the generously proportioned windows and reflects off the polished floors and stone bench tops. This free-flowing area easily accommodates everything from big get-togethers to games nights or casual family meals all year round. In warm weather, slide back the large glass doors to reveal an undercover alfresco dining deck perfect for sunny lunches or summer nights. Formal occasions are well catered for as well, with the central grand island kitchen bench just made for serving, and the large butler?s pantry perfect for preparation and storage. The formal dining room is nearby and has easy access to the downstairs powder room for guests? convenience. Upstairs, everyone has his or her own personal space; none more than the parents with a simply palatial master suite. An open area at the top of the stairs is suitable for a TV lounge or study area and leads to three bedrooms, all with built-in robes. The centrally located and spacious bathroom has a shower and bath plus separate powder room, so there?s no lining up! The sprawling master suite takes up the rest of the top floor. There?s a walk-in robe nearly as big as a bedroom with three sides of storage you?ll be challenged to fill. An ensuite with twin basins, separate toilet, large bath and extra-large shower gives you so much room you?ll think you are in a penthouse bathroom! If you?re looking for all that life can offer, there?s nothing as generous as the Mercer.

Life is too short to compromise - which is why the Geneva series makes it easy to have comfort, style and convenience all under the one roof.

Description:
Effortless style, integrated living zones and interior flair make the Carmelle a unique family home.

The carefully considered design with central integrated living, allows the family to come together for casual family meals and entertainment, yet still permits each member to enjoy their own space.

An emphasis on functionality is clearly reflected in the large laundry and well laid out kitchen. Sprawling from this central kitchen hub is a plethora of spacious living, dining, and entertainment spaces. Entertainment is very much on the agenda in this family home with indoor and outdoor dining options including an undercover alfresco as well as three more separate entertainment areas including a home theatre, kids retreat and living room.

The master bedroom at the front of the house also doubles as a parentss retreat and boasts a large walk-in wardrobe plus ensuite featuring his and her basins.

Three further bedrooms are located at the other end of the house, one with a walk-in robe, the others with built-in wardrobes to keep clothes neatly tucked away. These generously sized double bedrooms each open out onto a kid's retreat perfect for the kids to relax and play. The well-proportioned main bathroom with shower and bath is positioned across the hall from the powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Name: Mercer Q3 - Lot 2050 Carissa Road
Description:
Delightfully light, deceptively large and fully equipped with all the luxury touches, the Mercer is for families who like to live on a truly magnificent scale!

From the moment you step inside from the covered porch, you get a sense of just how grand this home is. A wide hallway leads you past a spacious study, huge home theatre and smart dining room to the open plan kitchen, living and dining area. Here the light floods in from the generously proportioned windows and reflects off the polished floors and stone bench tops. This free-flowing area easily accommodates everything from big get-togethers to games nights or casual family meals all year round.

In warm weather, slide back the large glass doors to reveal an undercover alfresco dining deck perfect for sunny lunches or summer nights.
Formal occasions are well catered for as well, with the central grand island kitchen bench just made for serving, and the large butler?s pantry perfect for preparation and storage. The formal dining room is nearby and has easy access to the downstairs powder room for guests? convenience.

Upstairs, everyone has his or her own personal space; none more than the parents with a simply palatial master suite. An open area at the top of the stairs is suitable for a TV lounge or study area and leads to three bedrooms, all with built-in robes. The centrally located and spacious bathroom has a shower and bath plus separate powder room, so there?s no lining up!

The sprawling master suite takes up the rest of the top floor. There?s a walk-in robe nearly as big as a bedroom with three sides of storage you?ll be challenged to fill. An ensuite with twin basins, separate toilet, large bath and extra-large shower gives you so much room you?ll think you are in a penthouse bathroom!

If you?re looking for all that life can offer, there?s nothing as generous as the Mercer.

Sprawling from this central kitchen hub is a plethora of spacious living, dining, and entertainment spaces. The master bedroom at the front of the house also doubles as a parentss retreat and boasts a large walk-in wardrobe plus ensuite featuring his and her basins.

Three further bedrooms are located at the other end of the house, one with a walk-in robe, the others with built-in wardrobes to keep clothes neatly tucked away. These generously sized double bedrooms each open out onto a kid's retreat perfect for the kids to relax and play. The well-proportioned main bathroom with shower and bath is positioned across the hall from the powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Life is too short to compromise - which is why the Geneva series makes it easy to have comfort, style and convenience all under the one roof.

Name: Lexington Vue Q1 - Lot 689 Pioneer Drive
Carmelle Q1 - Lot 619 Calibre Circuit
Description:
Effortless style, integrated living zones and interior flair make the Carmelle a unique family home.

The carefully considered design with central integrated living, allows the family to come together for casual family meals and entertainment, yet still permits each member to enjoy their own space.

An emphasis on functionality is clearly reflected in the large laundry and well laid out kitchen. The laundry has room for the biggest piles of washing and opens to the side of the house for easy access to the outdoors. Function and style continues into the kitchen with an impressive grand island bench that doubles as a breakfast bar and servery. Food and dishes can be kept out of sight in the butler's pantry, which is easily accessed from the garage for swift delivery of groceries. Generous bench space either side of the cooktop makes preparing large dinners a breeze.
Sprawling from this central kitchen hub is a plethora of spacious living, dining, and entertainment spaces. Entertainment is very much on the agenda in this family home with indoor and outdoor dining options including an undercover alfresco as well as three more separate entertainment areas including a home theatre, kids retreat and living room.

The master bedroom at the front of the house also doubles as a parentss retreat and boasts a large walk-in wardrobe plus ensuite featuring his and her basins.

Three further bedrooms are located at the other end of the house, one with a walk-in robe, the others with built-in wardrobes to keep clothes neatly tucked away. These generously sized double bedrooms each open out onto a kid's retreat perfect for the kids to relax and play. The well-proportioned main bathroom with shower and bath is positioned across the hall from the powder room, meaning more than one person can use the facilities at a time.

With a little something for everyone, the Carmelle offers functionality, comfort and style all under the one roof.

Name: Marina Q1 - Lot 303 Beckworth Boulevard
Description:
Everything about the Marina is designed for effortless family living. Practical touches like a spacious butler?s pantry hidden from view behind the kitchen, integrated, open-plan living spaces and smaller, but just as important, features like the generous walk-in-linen closet make this home easy to live in and love.

The whole family will enjoy meals and gatherings in the open plan living-dining-kitchen area. The stunning, stone island kitchen

bench is a focal point and doubles as a breakfast bar or servery when entertaining. In keeping with the practical nature of this home, there?s a large butler?s pantry behind the kitchen for food storage and preparation and a place to hide away the fridge.

If a little peace and quiet is needed, family members can retreat to the home theatre down the hall, which is neatly positioned between the sleeping zones. This flexible room can be used for watching movies, playing games, studying, music or relaxing.
Parents will enjoy their own space with a generous master suite conveniently placed at the front for seclusion and light. Featuring a large walk-in robe and an ensuite with separate toilet and twin basins, this functional area also offers a touch of luxury.

Three more bedrooms are positioned to the rear of the home and all feature built in robes to help keep rooms neat and spacious. A centrally located bathroom is appointed with vanity, bath and shower plus a separate powder room. This means no queuing for the facilities ? which is sure to result in a peaceful household! The powder room also provides convenience for guests when entertaining. A large, centrally located linen closet provides extra storage ? yet another practical addition to this home.

With an abundance of well-placed practical features, the Marina is an easy living, stylish family home.

Name: Monterey Nouveau Q1 Mk2 - Lot 947 Yan Yean Avenue
Description:
An energetically modern and chic single storey home that offers all the luxuries and superior features previously only available in a large double storey home, makes the Monterey Series a best seller in its own right.

 Upon entering the Monterey, you will inevitably notice its ingenious and contemporary design. At the front of the home, take some time out in the plush atmosphere of the master suite, with its own walk-in robe and a striking ensuite offering a double vanity and secluded large shower. Only a few steps away from the master suite, you will find the study, ideal for a quiet moment away from it all.

 Stroll out and you will be greeted by a luxurious living area, leading you into the hub of this home. Surrounded by a theatre, dining, living and undercover alfresco area, the dazzling designer kitchen will become the perfect backdrop for the globe-trotting master chef wanting to whip up that secret signature dish.
 And for those with too many recipes to remember, and an even longer list of friends wanting a taste, the Monterey offers a generous butler?s pantry for added storage room for large dinner parties. The Monterey Series is the idyllic choice for families in need of space with secondary double-sized bedrooms all with built-in robes. A bathroom with a deep bath and separate toilet is another thoughtful touch for a growing family.

 The Monterey Nouveau Q1 also offers additional space for a home frequently visited by friends, family and neighbours, boasting an extra powder room and additional hallway that connects all the bedrooms while also separating them from the livelier entertaining areas. This makes the Monterey a serene haven, encapsulating elegant, inspired design.
